==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# [[verbal|Verbal]] [[impudence]] or [[argumentative]] discourse, given in [[response]].
#:''Don't give me any '''backtalk'''; just go clean your room.''

====Synonyms====
*(''verbal impudence or argument''): [[derision]], [[lip]], [[sass]], [[rebuttal]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}
# To [[respond]] in a [[disputative]], often [[sarcastic]] manner.
#:''Peter was sent to detention for '''backtalking''' the teacher.''

====Synonyms====
*(''disputatively or sarcastically respond''): [[mouth off]], [[sass]]